  Mark stable on amd64 wrt bug #525148

*mpv-0.9.1 (03 May 2015)

  03 May 2015; Ben de Groot <yngwin@gentoo.org> +mpv-0.9.1.ebuild,
  -mpv-0.3.11-r1.ebuild, -mpv-0.7.3.ebuild:
  version bump; remove old

  31 Mar 2015; Maxim Koltsov <maksbotan@gentoo.org> metadata.xml,
  mpv-9999.ebuild:
  Ebuild update by Nikoli: cosmetic fixes, added useflag for raspberry pi. Added
  myself to metadata to make it clear that package is maintained in close
  collaboration.

  28 Mar 2015; Ben de Groot <yngwin@gentoo.org> -mpv-0.8.0.ebuild,
  -mpv-0.8.2.ebuild, mpv-0.7.3.ebuild, mpv-0.8.3.ebuild, mpv-9999.ebuild:
  Update live ebuild to sync with upstream changes, as reported by Nikos
  Chantziaras in bug #544402. Normalize useflags. Do not default enable mpg123,
  as upstream recommends libavcodec. Remove older 0.8.x ebuilds.

  19 Mar 2015; Ben de Groot <yngwin@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Add myself as maintainer

  19 Mar 2015; Ben de Groot <yngwin@gentoo.org> mpv-0.8.3.ebuild,
  mpv-9999.ebuild:
  Add message about upstream recommendation for ffmpeg. Add more license
  information (bug #506946). Remove useless - for doc-pdf useflag again.
  Reformat lines for live ebuild. Move some stuff from src_unpack to
  src_prepare.

